cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.DS

The paper proposes a scalable multi-objective optimization algorithm using Bayesian neural networks, which is a common approach in machine learning and falls under the category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The algorithm also incorporates gradient information, which is a common technique in optimization and falls under the category of "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence). The use of Monte Carlo dropout and Sobolov training also suggests a connection to "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The algorithm is designed to handle large-scale optimization problems, which suggests a connection to "cs.SY" (Systems and Control) and "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms).
